### Health
GET http://localhost:3000/health

### Vision: base64 JSON (replace <BASE64>)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/vision/base64
Content-Type: application/json

{
	"image_base64": "<BASE64>",
	"mime": "image/jpeg",
	"prompt": "Describe this image"
}

### Vision: multipart upload (requires VS Code REST Client: @image refers to a file path)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/vision/upload
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=MyBoundary

--MyBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="image"; filename="sample.jpg"
Content-Type: image/jpeg

@c:/path/to/sample.jpg
--MyBoundary--

### Vision: raw JPEG (curl example below)
# No REST Client direct raw body include, use curl:
# curl -X POST "http://localhost:3000/api/vision/raw" ^
#   -H "Content-Type: image/jpeg" ^
#   --data-binary @c:/path/to/sample.jpg

